---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Kenius — Boutique AI consultancy · Strategy & implementation" description="Kenius is a boutique AI consultancy. Strategy first — we find where AI actually pays off in your business — then we design and build the implementation, quietly, into the tools you already use." path="/">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="hero-top reveal">
          <span class="cap">Kenius — Boutique AI consultancy</span>
          <span class="cap avail"><span class="dot"></span> Taking new work · 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h1>We find where AI <span class="it mark">belongs.</span> Then we build it.</h1>
        <div class="hero-foot">
          <div class="reveal" data-d="1">
            <p class="lead">Kenius is a boutique AI consultancy. Strategy first: we learn how you work and find where AI actually pays off. Then we build the implementation ourselves — quietly, into the tools you already use.</p>
            <div class="hero-actions" style="margin-top:2.2rem">
              <a class="tlink" href="/contact">Book a discovery call <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
              <a class="tlink tlink--bronze" href="#work">See the playbooks</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="justify-self:start" class="reveal" data-d="2">
            <span class="scroll-cue"><span class="cap">Scroll</span><span class="ln"></span></span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- OPS LEDGER — the "system" voice under the editorial thesis -->
        <div class="ledger" role="group" aria-label="Illustrative log of the kind of moments the agents we build handle, around the clock">
          <div class="ledger-head">
            <span class="cap"><span class="dot"></span> What the agents we build handle</span>
            <span class="cap ledger-meta">24/7 · illustrative</span>
          </div>
          <ol class="ledger-rows">
            <li><time>06:39</time><span class="dom">accounting</span><span class="msg">“still need my W-2?”</span><span class="st">docs collected</span></li>
            <li><time>05:41</time><span class="dom">law</span><span class="msg">after-hours injury call</span><span class="st">consult booked</span></li>
            <li><time>03:07</time><span class="dom">e-commerce</span><span class="msg">“where’s my order #8841?”</span><span class="st">tracking sent</span></li>
            <li><time>02:14</time><span class="dom">property-mgmt</span><span class="msg">“no heat — unit 4B”</span><span class="st">dispatched</span></li>
            <li><time>01:52</time><span class="dom">hvac</span><span class="msg">“furnace died, no heat”</span><span class="st">tech en route</span></li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="wrap rule reveal" />

    <!-- MANIFESTO -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap split">
        <div class="col-head reveal">
          <span class="cap cap--ink">Why now</span>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal" data-d="1">
          <p class="big">Most of your team’s day is <span class="soft">repeatable.</span> We work out which parts AI should take — and build them so they hold up in the real world, not just in a demo.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SERVICES INDEX -->
    <section class="section" id="services">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="index-head reveal">
          <span class="cap cap--ink">Services</span>
          <span class="cap">Six disciplines</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:var(--t-h2);max-width:14ch;margin-bottom:clamp(2rem,4vw,3.5rem)">What we do.</h2>
        <div class="idx">
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/services#consulting">
            <span class="num">01</span>
            <span class="ttl">AI strategy &amp; <span class="it">consulting</span></span>
            <span class="desc">We assess where AI pays off and hand you a clear, costed plan — even if the honest answer is “not yet.”</span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/services#agents">
            <span class="num">02</span>
            <span class="ttl">Custom AI agents</span>
            <span class="desc">Bespoke agents that complete whole tasks across your tools, and ask a human before anything risky.</span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/services#voice">
            <span class="num">03</span>
            <span class="ttl">Conversational &amp; <span class="it">voice AI</span></span>
            <span class="desc">Chat and phone assistants that understand people and get things booked — 24/7, in a voice you approve.</span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/services#automation">
            <span class="num">04</span>
            <span class="ttl">Document &amp; process automation</span>
            <span class="desc">Read, extract, enter and reconcile — the data entry that eats your afternoons just happens.</span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/services#copilots">
            <span class="num">05</span>
            <span class="ttl">Custom copilots</span>
            <span class="desc">An assistant grounded in your company’s own knowledge, living in the tools your team already uses.</span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/services#integrations">
            <span class="num">06</span>
            <span class="ttl">Integration &amp; data</span>
            <span class="desc">The unglamorous part that makes it all work: connecting your systems so the AI can actually act.</span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DARK INTERLUDE -->
    <section class="section dark" id="approach">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="cap reveal">Approach</span>
        <p class="big-statement reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:1.5rem">We advise first. <span class="it">Then we build.</span></p>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step reveal"><span class="n">WK 0</span><h3>Assess</h3><p>We map the busywork and recommend the one place to start with the best payoff — honestly.</p></div>
          <div class="step reveal" data-d="1"><span class="n">WK 1–2</span><h3>Prototype</h3><p>A working version on your real data you can try in about two weeks — not a slide deck.</p></div>
          <div class="step reveal" data-d="2"><span class="n">WK 4–8</span><h3>Build</h3><p>Wired into your tools, tested against the edge cases, with guardrails and a human-approval step.</p></div>
          <div class="step reveal" data-d="3"><span class="n">HANDOVER</span><h3>Hand over</h3><p>We measure the hours saved, tune it, and give you the keys. Fixed scope, no lock-in.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- INDUSTRIES INDEX -->
    <section class="section" id="industries">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="index-head reveal">
          <span class="cap cap--ink">Playbooks</span>
          <span class="cap">Where AI pays off</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idx">
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/work#property">
            <span class="num">/01</span><span class="ttl">Property management</span>
            <span class="desc log"><time>02:14</time> “no heat — unit 4B” <span class="st">→ dispatched</span></span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/work#real-estate">
            <span class="num">/02</span><span class="ttl">Real estate</span>
            <span class="desc log"><time>18:22</time> portal lead · pre-approved <span class="st">→ tour booked</span></span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/work#law">
            <span class="num">/03</span><span class="ttl">Law firms</span>
            <span class="desc log"><time>03:51</time> after-hours injury call <span class="st">→ consult booked</span></span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/work#accounting">
            <span class="num">/04</span><span class="ttl">Accounting &amp; CPA</span>
            <span class="desc log"><time>06:39</time> “still need my W-2?” <span class="st">→ docs collected</span></span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/work#home-services">
            <span class="num">/05</span><span class="ttl">Home services &amp; trades</span>
            <span class="desc log"><time>23:58</time> missed call · furnace out <span class="st">→ tech en route</span></span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a class="idx-row reveal" href="/work#freight">
            <span class="num">/06</span><span class="ttl">Freight &amp; logistics</span>
            <span class="desc log"><time>04:12</time> “where’s my load #LT-4471?” <span class="st">→ ETA sent</span></span>
            <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SELECTED WORK -->
    <section class="section" id="work">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="index-head reveal">
          <h2 style="font-size:var(--t-h2)">What we build, in practice.</h2>
          <span class="cap">Recurring builds · no two alike</span>
        </div>
        <div class="work">
          <article class="work-row reveal">
            <div>
              <div class="wmeta"><span class="cap">Voice · front desk</span></div>
              <h3>The phone that answers itself.</h3>
              <p>A voice agent that picks up 24/7 in a voice you approve — books the routine, takes messages, and patches real emergencies straight through to a person.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="metrics">
              <p class="cap" style="color:var(--muted);max-width:26ch;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:.02em;font-family:var(--mono)">→ after-hours calls booked, not lost</p>
            </div>
          </article>
          <article class="work-row reveal">
            <div>
              <div class="wmeta"><span class="cap">Inbox · support</span></div>
              <h3>Support that keeps up with sales.</h3>
              <p>An assistant trained on your policies that resolves the repetitive tickets — order status, returns, the same five questions — and hands the tricky ones to your team with full context.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="metrics">
              <p class="cap" style="color:var(--muted);max-width:26ch;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:.02em;font-family:var(--mono)">→ the routine resolved; people on the exceptions</p>
            </div>
          </article>
          <article class="work-row reveal">
            <div>
              <div class="wmeta"><span class="cap">Documents · back office</span></div>
              <h3>Paperwork that files itself.</h3>
              <p>Automation that reads invoices, forms and receipts, enters them into the systems you already run, and flags only the odd ones for a human eye.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="metrics">
              <p class="cap" style="color:var(--muted);max-width:26ch;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:.02em;font-family:var(--mono)">→ afternoons back; only exceptions reviewed</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
        <p class="reveal" style="margin-top:2.5rem"><a class="tlink" href="/work">All industry playbooks <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PULL QUOTE -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap quote reveal">
        <blockquote>“We’d rather tell you <span class="it">not yet</span> than build something that doesn’t pay for itself.”</blockquote>
        <div class="by"><span class="cap cap--ink">The advising-first principle</span><br /><span class="cap">How every Kenius engagement starts</span></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUESTIONS -->
    <section class="section" id="faq">
      <div class="wrap split">
        <div class="col-head reveal"><span class="cap cap--ink">Questions</span></div>
        <div class="faq reveal" data-d="1">
          <details>
            <summary>Do you sell a product, or build custom?<span class="pl" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="ans">We’re a consultancy. We don’t resell a one-size tool — we assess what your business needs, build the right solution around your data, and hand it over so you own it.</div>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Where do we start if we’re unsure?<span class="pl" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="ans">With a short assessment. In a week or two we map your workflows, find the highest-value opportunity, and give you a costed plan — no obligation to build anything afterwards.</div>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Is our data safe?<span class="pl" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="ans">Your data stays yours. We don’t sell it or use it to train public models; access is scoped to the job, everything is logged, and you can revoke it any time.</div>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What does it cost?<span class="pl" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="ans">The assessment and pilots are fixed-fee, so you know the number up front. We prove the value on one use case, then expand.</div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="wrap rule reveal" />

    <!-- CONTACT -->
    <section class="section contact" id="contact">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="cap reveal">Contact</span>
        <h2 class="reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:1.4rem">Start with a <span class="it">conversation.</span></h2>
        <div class="reveal" data-d="1">
          <a class="big-mail" href="mailto:hello@kenius.us">hello@kenius.us</a>
        </div>
        <p class="reveal" data-d="2" style="margin-top:2rem"><a class="tlink" href="/contact">Or book a 30-minute discovery call <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></p>
        <p class="cap reveal" data-d="2" style="margin-top:2.5rem">We reply within one business day · Remote-first</p>
      </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
